An 86-year-old Port Richey man is dead after a collision Monday afternoon on Ridge Road in Pasco County. The man drove his sedan onto Ridge Road from a private driveway located east of Regency Park Boulevard around 12:08 p.m., the Florida Highway Patrol said in a news release. At the same time, a 38-year-old New Port Richey woman was driving a sedan westbound on Ridge Road, and the front of her sedan struck the left side of the manâ€™s sedan, troopers said. The 86-year-old man died at the scene of the crash, according to the news release. The 38-year-old woman sustained minor injuries. The Highway Patrol did not provide the names of either driver.